headline: Rail Regulator Sends $71.5 Billion Union Pacific-Norfolk Southern Deal Back for Redo
summary: The Surface Transportation Board has said that the application is incomplete and is inviting the companies to revise and resubmit it.

headline: STB rejects “incomplete” UP-NS merger application
summary: The Surface Transportation Board rejected as incomplete the merger application by Union Pacific and Norfolk Southern to create the first transcontinental railroad. The post STB rejects “incomplete” UP-NS merger application appeared first on FreightWaves.
